<p>This gorgeous lime and coconut tart is actually a really old recipe of mine. I cooked and shot it a long time ago but for some reason, I thought I had lost the photos so I never posted it on the blog. Well, last week, while doing some digital decluttering, I found the original photos on one of my drives. I was so excited because I remember how much I enjoyed this tart.</p>
<p>The tart has a nutty, biscuit-like base (think a cheesecake) and custardy filling made with lots of lime juicy, creamy coconut and eggs. The recipe uses gluten-free, grain-free, low-carb ingredients but it certainly doesn&#8217;t lack in flavour. It&#8217;s quite tropical and isn&#8217;t overly sweet. I use Stevia as a sweetener to keep it low in sugar and carbohydrates, but you can use honey or coconut syrup.</p>
<div class="content_hint">&nbsp;</div>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="alignnone wp-image-136624 size-full" src="https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/paleo-tart-coconut-lime-3.jpg" alt="Paleo Lime &amp; Coconut Tart" width="800" height="1200" data-pin-title="Paleo Lime &amp; Coconut Tart" data-pin-description="Tropical and light, this gluten-free, paleo lime and coconut tart has a nutty crust and custard-like filling. Topped with toasted shredded coconut for that perfect crunchy finish. It's a great low-carb, paleo dessert that is perfect for any occasion. #tart #limetart #coconut #paleo #paleodesserts #paleocakes #paleotart #paleobaking #glutenfree #grainfree #dessert #sweettreat #tropical " srcset="https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/paleo-tart-coconut-lime-3.jpg 800w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/paleo-tart-coconut-lime-3-200x300.jpg 200w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/paleo-tart-coconut-lime-3-683x1024.jpg 683w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/paleo-tart-coconut-lime-3-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/paleo-tart-coconut-lime-3-123x185.jpg 123w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></p>
<h2>How to make paleo tart pastry&nbsp;</h2>
<p>Unfortunately, I didn&#8217;t take any step-by-step photos at the time but I&#8217;ve got a few reference pics for what you&#8217;re aiming for with the tart tin pastry case below (<a href="https://www.leiths.com/how-tos/how-to-make-a-flat-tin-pastry-case">from Leiths.com</a>).</p>
<p>As this is a grain-free and gluten-free tart, the pastry dough has a slightly different texture and has to be handled carefully. Once you combine the mixture and knead the pastry dough, it will be soft but pliable. It&#8217;s a little fragile to roll out with a pin, as you would for a tart casing. So, you have to <strong>treat dough like playdough</strong> and use your hands to line it over the tart tin and press it down into the sides. You will find more detailed instructions in<strong> the recipe card below.</strong></p>
<p>Once you&#8217;ve made the casing <strong>refrigerate it for 15-20 minutes</strong> and then you have to &#8216;blind bake&#8217; it. This means baking it empty without a filling but you need to add a piece of parchment paper and something heavy inside. You can use dried beans or chickpeas or small stones. Then you finish baking the tart with the filling inside.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-pin-description="Tropical and light, this gluten-free, paleo lime and coconut tart has a nutty crust and custard-like filling. Topped with toasted coconut for that perfect crunchy finish. #tart #limetart #coconut #paleo #paleodesserts #paleocakes #paleotart #paleobaking #glutenfree #grainfree #dessert #sweettreat #tropical" data-pin-title="Lime &amp; Coconut Tart (Paleo, Gluten-Free, Low-Carb)" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-136620" src="https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/how-to-make-tart-pastry.jpg" alt="How to make paleo tart pastry" width="1200" height="400" data-pin-nopin="true" srcset="https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/how-to-make-tart-pastry.jpg 1200w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/how-to-make-tart-pastry-300x100.jpg 300w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/how-to-make-tart-pastry-1024x341.jpg 1024w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/how-to-make-tart-pastry-768x256.jpg 768w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/how-to-make-tart-pastry-185x62.jpg 185w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /></p>
<div class="content_hint">&nbsp;</div>
<h3>WHAT KIND OF TART TIN TO USE?</h3>
<p>Once the tart is baked, allow cooling completely before attempting to slice it. I usually let it cool in the baking tin before transferring to a platter. My tip is to use a <a href="https://amzn.to/2OnWdNc" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">tart tin with a removable bottom</a> as it makes it so much easier. A 9-inch tart tin is perfect but you could also use a smaller, deeper tin or individual tartlet tins (in this case, reduce the cooking time in both stages).</p>
<p>You will find further notes on ingredients and cooking tips in the recipe card below.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" data-pin-description="Tropical and light, this gluten-free, paleo lime and coconut tart has a nutty crust and custard-like filling. Topped with toasted coconut for that perfect crunchy finish. #tart #limetart #coconut #paleo #paleodesserts #paleocakes #paleotart #paleobaking #glutenfree #grainfree #dessert #sweettreat #tropical" data-pin-title="Lime &amp; Coconut Tart (Paleo, Gluten-Free, Low-Carb)" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-136619" src="https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/gluten-free-tart-lime-coconut-2.jpg" alt="Gluten-Free Tart With Lime &amp; Coconut Filling" width="800" height="533" data-pin-nopin="true" srcset="https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/gluten-free-tart-lime-coconut-2.jpg 800w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/gluten-free-tart-lime-coconut-2-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/gluten-free-tart-lime-coconut-2-600x400.jpg 600w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/gluten-free-tart-lime-coconut-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.cookedandloved.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/gluten-free-tart-lime-coconut-2-185x123.jpg 185w" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" /></p>
<h3>STORING THE TART</h3>
<p>This tart should ideally be stored in an airtight container or covered with a plate in the refrigerator. It will keep for 4-5 days.</p>
<h3>MORE PALEO TREATS TO EXPLORE</h3>
